   <body>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA"><a name="DUCdafaf1802ae710058dcd8dcc6a5141d2"></a>Removing the front wheel
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3613"> </a>Support the bike so that the front wheel is raised from the ground.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3615"> </a>Remove the front brake calliper (B) by unscrewing the two screws (A) securing the calliper to the fork leg; do not disconnect
            the calliper from the hose.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_000103093.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_000203094.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/warning.jpg">Warning
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3622"> </a>Do not operate the brake lever when the callipers are removed. This can cause the brake pistons to be expelled.
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3625"> </a>Loosen and remove the nut (1) on left side of the axle.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3627"> </a>Recover the washer (2).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_000303095.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3632"> </a>Loosen the wheel shaft screws (8) on the fork legs.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_002103103.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_002203104.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3639"> </a>Working from the left-hand side, use a plastic mallet to drive the axle (4) out from the opposite side and remove it.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_000703099.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3645"> </a>Remove the wheel and recover the spacers (5) and (6).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_000803100.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_000903101.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3652"> </a>Working from both sides, remove the oil sealing ring (7).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
